  19 Jul 2005; Bryan Østergaard <kloeri@gentoo.org>
  sysfsutils-1.2.0-r2.ebuild:
  Stable on alpha.

  18 Jul 2005; Joseph Jezak <josejx@gentoo.org> sysfsutils-1.2.0-r2.ebuild:
  Marked ppc stable.

  12 Jul 2005; Simon Stelling <blubb@gentoo.org> sysfsutils-1.2.0-r2.ebuild:
  stable on amd64

  03 Jul 2005; Olivier Crête <tester@gentoo.org>
  sysfsutils-1.2.0-r2.ebuild:
  Stable on x86 per bug 82970

  03 Jul 2005; Rene Nussbaumer <killerfox@gentoo.org>
  sysfsutils-1.2.0-r2.ebuild:
  Stable on hppa. bug 82970

*sysfsutils-1.3.0 (03 Jul 2005)

  03 Jul 2005; Martin Schlemmer <azarah@gentoo.org>
  +sysfsutils-1.3.0.ebuild:
  Update version.

*sysfsutils-1.2.0-r3 (03 Jul 2005)

  03 Jul 2005; Martin Schlemmer <azarah@gentoo.org>
  +sysfsutils-1.2.0-r3.ebuild:
  Add linker script to fix newer gcc only linking to static lib if .so's in
  /lib and .a in /usr/lib, bug #4411. Do not use absolute symlink for libtool
  linker script.

  03 Jul 2005; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  sysfsutils-1.2.0-r2.ebuild:
  Made multilib-strict aware.

  03 Jul 2005; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org>
  sysfsutils-1.2.0-r2.ebuild:
  stable on ia64 #82970

  03 Jul 2005; Markus Rothe <corsair@gentoo.org> sysfsutils-1.2.0-r2.ebuild:
  Stable on ppc64 (bug #82970)

*sysfsutils-1.2.0-r2 (02 Jul 2005)

  02 Jul 2005; Robin H. Johnson <robbat2@gentoo.org>
  +sysfsutils-1.2.0-r2.ebuild:
  Add small fix for -r2 that installs shared libs in /lib to allow for usage
  before /usr is available. See bug #82970 for information.

*sysfsutils-1.2.0-r1 (20 May 2005)

  20 May 2005; <brix@gentoo.org>
  +files/sysfsutils-1.2.0-write-attribute.patch,
  +sysfsutils-1.2.0-r1.ebuild:
  Added write_attribute() patch fixing bug #84228.

  01 Apr 2005; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> sysfsutils-1.2.0.ebuild:
  stable on ia64

  08 Mar 2005; Tom Gall <tgall@gentoo.org> sysfsutils-1.2.0.ebuild:
  stable on ppc64, used as part of iprutils

  03 Mar 2005; Markus Rothe <corsair@gentoo.org> sysfsutils-1.2.0.ebuild:
  Added ~ppc64 to KEYWORDS; bug #83939

  31 Dec 2004; Bryan Østergaard <kloeri@gentoo.org>
  sysfsutils-1.2.0.ebuild:
  ~alpha keyword.

  17 Dec 2004; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org> sysfsutils-1.2.0.ebuild:
  Stripped problematic elibtoolize calls. No longer uses einstall. Closes bug #74631.

*sysfsutils-1.2.0 (08 Nov 2004)

  08 Nov 2004; Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@gentoo.org> metadata.xml,
  +sysfsutils-1.2.0.ebuild:
  1.2.0 release
  ugh, make me the maintainer, like I don't have anything else better to do...

  01 Jul 2004; Jeremy Huddleston <eradicator@gentoo.org>
  sysfsutils-0.2.0.ebuild, sysfsutils-0.3.0.ebuild, sysfsutils-0.4.0.ebuild,
  sysfsutils-1.0.0.ebuild:
  virtual/glibc -> virtual/libc

  22 Mar 2004; Joshua Kinard <kumba@gentoo.org> sysfsutils-1.0.0.ebuild:
  Added ~mips to KEYWORDS and added gnuconfig support for mips.

*sysfsutils-1.0.0 (29 Feb 2004)

  29 Feb 2004; Martin Schlemmer <azarah@gentoo.org> sysfsutils-1.0.0.ebuild,
  files/sysfsutils-1.0.0-dont-check-for-libsysfs.patch:
  Update version. Do not check for external libsysfs, else it links systool, etc
  against old libsysfs as well if older sysfsutils is installed.

  26 Feb 2004; Ciaran McCreesh <ciaranm@gentoo.org> sysfsutils-0.4.0.ebuild:
  Seems happy on sparc

